sql:
SELECT file_size
FROM image_files
ORDER BY file_size DESC;

external_knowledge:
; Image analysis often involves complex metrics and class hierarchies, requiring recursive queries to unravel relationships between different classes and their confidence thresholds; 
; Model performance metrics (accuracy, F1 score, precision, recall) are critical in evaluating the effectiveness of models in image classification tasks;
; Understanding access patterns (total accesses, downloads) and annotation quality (confidence levels) can provide insights into data usage and reliability.

- Accuracy refers to the proportion of correctly classified images; 
- F1 score is the harmonic mean of precision and recall, where precision is the ratio of true positives to the sum of true positives and false positives, and recall is the ratio of true positives to the sum of true positives and false negatives; 
- A high F1 score indicates good performance on both precision and recall; 
- In the context of image classification, a maximum accuracy threshold of 0.90 may be used to filter out poorly performing models.
